<br>
I get groups all the time.<br>
<br>
Monks are great additions to groups.  They stack well on raids.<br>
<br>
I often get tells from across zones to join groups just because I have my LFG tag on.<br>
<br>
If you are a good person and a smart player, groups will love you.<br>
<br>
If you are there to pull, pull well.<br>
<br>
If you are there to deal damage, do it and try not to get aggro.  Someone dishing out monkly damage that doesn't need mana for heals is an asset to any group.<br>
<br>
If your shaman is low mana, bandage him up while he canabilizes.  He or she will love you for it.<br>
<br>
I don't know, maybe it is because I am a cheap slut, but I rarely have the difficulties expressed here getting into groups.<br>
<br>
Oh, it also helps if you have a belly button. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
